OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FOnly in Westminster could a King
OL,7,Fwearing a crown arriving in a horse-
OL,8,Fdrawn golden carriage to sit on an
OL,9,Fopulent throne be the sideshow to a
OL,10,Fbloke called Wes and whether he'll
OL,11,Fquit his job.
OL,13,FThe actual laws the government wants
OL,14,Fto change in the country are merely a
OL,15,Fdistraction from the main event - Keir
OL,16,Fv Wes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FThe King's Speech does matter, though
OL,7,F- what's in it should mean something -
OL,8,Fbecause it gives a glimpse into why
OL,9,Four political system appears in a
OL,10,Fcycle of constant chaos, the feeling
OL,11,Fin the country of terminal decline,
OL,12,Fwith voters increasingly sick of the
OL,13,Flot of them.
OL,15,FTake housing, which featured in the
OL,16,Flist of legislative changes King
OL,17,FCharles read out in Parliament on
OL,18,FWednesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FSo many of Britain's current problems
OL,7,Flead back to housing - the lack of it,
OL,8,Fthe cost of it, the state of it,
OL,9,Faccess to it.
OL,11,FAs Rachel Williamson puts it in her
OL,12,Freport, Housing, populism, and the
OL,13,Fpolitics of belonging, "housing has
OL,14,Fbecome a highly charged
OL,15,Fissue...transcending its traditional
OL,16,Frole as a matter of building homes to
OL,17,Ftouch on people's deeper feelings of
OL,18,Ffairness, identity, and belonging.
OL,26,@uD@XOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,F"The way housing issues are discussed
OL,7,Fand amplified on social media has
OL,8,Fbecome a significant factor in shaping
OL,9,Fpublic opinion and influencing the
OL,10,Fpolitical landscape."
OL,12,FTurns out that if you don't build
OL,13,Fenough homes for 45 years, and sell
OL,14,Foff the affordable ones (council
OL,15,Fhousing) without replacing them, you
OL,16,Fend up with a problem.
OL,26,@rD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FA crisis, even. A proper crisis, where
OL,7,Fpeople are made homeless and live in
OL,8,Fdangerous flats that make their
OL,9,Fchildren sick and can't afford to move
OL,10,Fanywhere safe or decent.
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FBack to the political sideshow that is
OL,7,Fthe King's Speech, then, where the
OL,8,Fgovernment has included the Social
OL,9,FHousing Renewal Bill, which attempts
OL,10,Fto tackle a crisis in housing stock
OL,11,Fthat is contributing towards record
OL,12,Flevels of child homelessness and a
OL,13,Fwaiting list north of 1.3 million
OL,14,Fhouseholds, which in turn is
OL,15,Ftriggering difficult questions of who
OL,16,Fshould be able to access what precious
OL,17,Fsocial housing we still have.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FThe Bill would make some important
OL,7,Fchanges. As well as greater
OL,8,Fprotections for victims of domestic
OL,9,Fabuse in social housing, for the first
OL,10,Ftime since Margaret Thatcher
OL,11,Fintroduced the Right to Buy scheme in
OL,12,Fits modern form, tighter restrictions
OL,13,Fwill be placed on tenants wanting to
OL,14,Fbuy their social homes.
OL,16,FNewly-built social homes will be
OL,17,Fexempt from purchase by the tenant for
OL,18,F35 years, and eligibility for existing
OL,19,Fhomes will be made stricter.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FThis is recognition that far too many
OL,7,Fsocial homes (the most affordable)
OL,8,Fhave been lost in the last five
OL,9,Fdecades, and the first real attempt to
OL,10,Fdo something about it, falling short
OL,11,Fof scrapping Right to Buy altogether
OL,12,F(which even former Housing Secretary
OL,13,FAngela Rayner once told me she would
OL,14,Fnever do).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,F"The government also wants to
OL,7,Fincentivise councils to build more
OL,8,Fhomes, both by ensuring they would not
OL,9,Fbe sold and by repealing measures
OL,10,Fbrought in by the previous
OL,11,FConservative governments requiring
OL,12,Fcouncils to sell high-value homes and
OL,13,Fto charge higher-income tenants higher
OL,14,Frents.
OL,16,FAll of that will be backed up with #39
OL,17,Fbillion over the next ten years for
OL,18,Fnew affordable homes, 60% of them for
OL,19,Fsocial rent, a considerable increase
OL,20,Fon previous housing programmes.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FIs it enough to tackle the crisis in
OL,7,Fhousing affordability? In short, no.
OL,8,FThe programme will see 300,000 new
OL,9,Fhomes built in the next decade,
OL,10,F180,000 of them social homes.
OL,12,FThe housing sector welcomes it,
OL,13,Fbroadly, as a step in the right
OL,14,Fdirection, but it isn't the bold and
OL,15,Fambitious plan that we saw the 1945
OL,16,FLabour government embark on, and every
OL,17,Fgovernment that followed up to 1979.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FAs the charity Shelter put it: "The
OL,7,Fgovernment promised a council and
OL,8,Fsocial housing revolution...and we're
OL,9,Fstill waiting."
OL,11,FThey say 90,000 are needed each year
OL,12,Fto meet current demand, and are
OL,13,Fcalling for a new generation of social
OL,14,Fhomes: "History shows we can't get
OL,15,Fthere without councils building at
OL,16,Fscale."
OL,18,FAnd so we come back to the problems
OL,19,Fplaguing the prime minister.
OL,26,@nD@`OUqD@OO]vD@HOUxD@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FHe promised 'Change', and after 14
OL,7,Fyears of Tory rule, expectations were
OL,8,Fhigh. Sir Keir Starmer pledged to
OL,9,Fbuild 1.5 million homes in this
OL,10,Fparliament. No one I speak to in
OL,11,Fhousing thinks this government - led
OL,12,Fby him or whoever else - will achieve
OL,13,Fthat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FMore importantly for affordability,
OL,7,Fhis government has never said how many
OL,8,Fof the 1.5 million will be social
OL,9,Fhomes, the kind of homes a Labour
OL,10,Fgovernment would be expected to build,
OL,11,Fthe only homes that can help the
OL,12,F176,000 children living in temporary
OL,13,Faccommodation in England and the
OL,14,Fmillions of people stuck in affordable
OL,15,Fand unsafe homes.
OL,17,FAs The i Paper's Vicky Spratt said on
OL,18,FMonday: "Politics will occupy the main
OL,19,Fstage this week, but really, Britain's
OL,20,Fproblems are policy problems."
OL,26,@zD@IOU|D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1778695869
OL,3,CWestminster psychodrama drowns out
OL,4,Cvital political housing reforms
OL,6,FOn housing policy, like in many other
OL,7,Fareas, there is a feeling the
OL,8,Fhandbrake remains on when it comes to
OL,9,Fmajor change - that Britain's systemic
OL,10,Fproblems are not being gripped, that
OL,11,FWestminster is not meeting the moment.
OL,13,FAnd so, unable to tackle the big
OL,14,Fpolicy issues, it once again takes
OL,15,Fcomfort in the personal and instead
OL,16,Fmakes political machinations the main
OL,17,Fact.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
